obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (10291)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title and commencement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_10_10_00011_200235_1517807322907&sectionId=10291&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_10_10_00011_200235_1517807322907
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the Haj Committee Act, 2002.`
  line
  line `(2) It shall come into force on such date^1`
  line `or dates as the Central Government may, by notification,`
  line `appoint, and different dates may be appointed for different provisions of this Act and for different States.`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. 5th December, 2002, vide notification No. S.O. 1267(E), dated by 5th December, 2002, see Gazette of India, Extraordinary,`
  line `Part II, sec. 3(ii).`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (10292)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_10_10_00011_200235_1517807322907&sectionId=10292&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_10_10_00011_200235_1517807322907
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires,--`
  line
  line `(a) "bye-laws" means the bye-laws made under section 45;`
  line
  line `(b) "Chief Executive Officer or the Executive Officer" means the Chief Executive Officer of the`
  line `Committee or the Executive Officer of the State Committee appointed under sub-section (1) of`
  line `section 16 or sub-section (1) of section 29, as the case may be;`
  line
  line `(c) "Committee" means the Haj Committee of India constituted under section 3;`
  line
  line `(d) "member" means a member of the Haj Committee of India nominated under section 4 or of a`
  line `State Haj Committee nominated under section 18, as the case may be, and includes the Chairperson`
  line `and a Vice-Chairperson;`
  line
  line `(e) "notification" means a notification published in the Gazette of India or the Official Gazette of`
  line `a State, as the case may be;`
  line
  line `(f) "pilgrim" means a Muslim proceeding to, or returning from, Haj;`
  line
  line `(g) "prescribed" means prescribed by rules made under section 44 by the Central Government or,`
  line `as the case may be, under section 47 by the State Government;`
  line
  line `(h) "State Committee" means a State Haj Committee constituted under section 18 and includes`
  line `Joint State Committee;`
  line
  line `(i) "State Government", in relation to a Union territory, means the Administrator of that Union`
  line `territory appointed by the President under article 239 of the Constitution.`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (10293)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Constitution and incorporation of Haj Committee of India.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_10_10_00011_200235_1517807322907&sectionId=10293&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_10_10_00011_200235_1517807322907
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `(1) With effect from such date as`
  line `the Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, appoint in this behalf, there shall be`
  line `constituted a Committee by the name of the Haj Committee of India.`
  line
  line `(2) The Committee shall be a body corporate, by the name aforesaid, having perpetual succession and`
  line `a common seal with power, subject to the provisions of this Act, to acquire, hold and dispose of property,`
  line `both movable and immovable, to create a charitable trust or endowment, and to contract and shall by the`
  line `said name sue and be sued.`
  line
  line `(3) The Committee shall have its headquarters at Mumbai and as and when the Committee considers`
  line `it functionally necessary, additional regional offices may be opened in consultation with the Central`
  line Government.
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (10294)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Composition of Committee.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_10_10_00011_200235_1517807322907&sectionId=10294&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_10_10_00011_200235_1517807322907
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `The Committee shall consist of the following members, namely:--`
  line
  line `(i) three members of Parliament of whom two are to be nominated by the Speaker of the House`
  line `of the People from among its Muslim members, and one by the Chairman of the Council of States`
  line `from among its Muslim members:`
  line
  line `Provided that a member of Parliament shall, upon ceasing to be a member, cease to be a`
  line `member of the Committee and the Speaker of the House of the People or the Chairman of the`
  line `Council of States, as the case may be, shall make a fresh nomination upon request by the Central`
  line Government;
  line
  line `(ii) nine Muslim members of the Committee shall be elected, three from those States sending`
  line `largest number of pilgrims during last three years and one each from the zones as specified in the`
  line `Schedule, in such manner as may be prescribed:`
  line
  line `Provided that not more than one member shall be elected from a State falling in the zone as`
  line `specified in the Schedule;`
  line
  line `(iii) four persons not below the rank of Joint Secretary to the Government of India nominated`
  line `by that Government to represent the Ministries of External Affairs, Home, Finance and Civil`
  line `Aviation, as ex officio members;`
  line
  line `(iv) seven Muslim members shall be nominated by the Central Government from among the`
  line `following categories of persons, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) two members who have special knowledge of public administration, finance, education,`
  line `culture or social work and out of whom one shall be a Shia Muslim;`
  line
  line `(b) two women members, out of them one shall be Shia Muslim;`
  line
  line `(c) three members who have special knowledge of Muslim theology and law, out of them one`
  line `shall be a Shia Muslim.`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (10295)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Notification of members.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_10_10_00011_200235_1517807322907&sectionId=10295&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_10_10_00011_200235_1517807322907
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `As soon as may be after the nomination of the members of the`
  line `Committee under section 4, the Central Government shall publish in the Official Gazette the names of all`
  line `such members.`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (10296)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Term of office.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_10_10_00011_200235_1517807322907&sectionId=10296&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_10_10_00011_200235_1517807322907
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `(1) The term of office of the members of the Committee (other than the ex officio members and members filling casual vacancies) shall be three years, commencing on the day following the publication of the list of members under section 5:`
  line
  line `Provided that the term of the members of the Committee may be extended by the Central Government`
  line `by a notification in the Official Gazette for a period not exceeding six months at a time but, in any case,`
  line `not exceeding beyond a total period of one year.`
  line
  line `(2) The allowances payable to, and the other terms and conditions of, the Chairperson,`
  line `Vice-Chairpersons and members shall be such as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (10297)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `Chairperson and Vice-Chairpersons.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_10_10_00011_200235_1517807322907&sectionId=10297&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_10_10_00011_200235_1517807322907
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `(1) After the publication of the names of members of the`
  line `Committee under section 5, the Central Government shall convene within forty-five days of such`
  line `publication the first meeting of the Committee at which the Committee shall elect a Chairperson and two`
  line `Vice-Chairpersons from amongst its members :`
  line
  line `Provided that a Minister shall not be the Chairperson of the Committee and ex officio members shall`
  line `not take part in the election of the Chairperson or of the Vice-Chairpersons.`
  line
  line `(2) If the Committee fails to elect the Chairperson or the Vice-Chairpersons the Central Government`
  line `may appoint a member of the Committee to be the Chairperson thereof or Vice-Chairpersons, as the case`
  line `may be.`
  line
  line `(3) The Chairperson shall exercise such powers and discharge such duties as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(4) The Vice-Chairpersons shall exercise such powers and discharge such duties as may be`
  line `determined by bye-laws made in this behalf by the Committee:`
  line
  line `Provided that till such bye-laws are made, the Vice-Chairpersons shall exercise such powers and`
  line `discharge such duties as may be determined by an order made by the Chairperson in this regard.`
  line
  line `(5) The election of the Chairperson and the Vice-Chairpersons shall be notified by the Central`
  line `Government in the Official Gazette.`
  line
  line `(6) The term of office of the Chairperson and the Vice-Chairpersons, as the case may be, shall be`
  line `co-terminus with the term of the Committee and no person shall hold office of the Chairperson or the`
  line `Vice-Chairpersons, as the case may be, for more than two consecutive terms.`
  line
  line `(7) Any casual vacancy in the office of the Chairperson or a Vice-Chairperson shall be filled for the`
  line `remainder of the term in accordance with sub-section (1) or sub-section (2), as the case may be.`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (10298)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title `Reconstitution of Committee.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_10_10_00011_200235_1517807322907&sectionId=10298&sectionno=8&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_10_10_00011_200235_1517807322907
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government shall take or cause to be taken all`
  line `necessary steps for the reconstitution of a new Committee at least four months before the expiry of the`
  line `term, or the extended term, as the case may be, of the committee.`
  line
  line `(2) An outgoing member shall be eligible for renomination on the Committee for not more than two`
  line `terms:`
  line
  line `Provided that not more than fifty per cent. of the members may be renominated for a second term in`
  line `such manner as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (10299)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 9
  title `Duties of Committee.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_10_10_00011_200235_1517807322907&sectionId=10299&sectionno=9&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_10_10_00011_200235_1517807322907
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `(1) The duties of the Committee shall be--`
  line
  line `(i) to collect and disseminate information useful to pilgrims, and to arrange orientation and`
  line `training programmes for pilgrims;`
  line
  line `(ii) to advise and assist pilgrims during their stay at the embarkation points in India, while`
  line `proceeding to or returning from pilgrimage, in all matters including vaccination, inoculation,`
  line `medical inspection, issue of pilgrim passes and foreign exchange, and to liaise with the local`
  line `authorities concerned in such matters;`
  line
  line `(iii) to give relief to pilgrims in distress;`
  line
  line `(iv) to finalise the annual Haj plan with the approval of the Central Government, and execute`
  line `the plan, including the arrangements for travel by air or any other means, and to advise in matters`
  line `relating to accommodations;`
  line
  line `(v) to approve the budget estimates of the Committee and submit it to the Central Government`
  line `at least three months before the beginning of the financial year for its concurrence;`
  line
  line `(vi) to co-ordinate with the Central Government, railways, airways and travel agencies for the`
  line `purpose of securing travelling facilities for pilgrims;`
  line
  line `(vii) to generally look after the welfare of the pilgrims;`
  line
  line `(viii) to publish such proceedings of the Committee and such matters of interest to pilgrims as`
  line `may be determined by bye-laws made in this behalf by the Committee;`
  line
  line `(ix) to discharge such other duties in connection with Haj as may be prescribed by the Central`
  line Government.
  line
  line `(2) The Central Government shall afford all reasonable assistance to the Committee in the discharge`
  line `of the duties specified in sub-section (1).`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (10300)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 10
  title `Meetings of Committee.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_10_10_00011_200235_1517807322907&sectionId=10300&sectionno=10&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_10_10_00011_200235_1517807322907
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Committee shall meet at least three times in a year before the`
  line `commencement of the Haj season to plan and make arrangements for Haj and once after that to review all`
  line `arrangements made by the Committee.`
  line
  line `(2) In addition to the meetings specified in sub-section (1), the Committee may hold meetings as and`
  line `when requisitioned by at least one-third of its members or when considered necessary by the Chairperson.`
  line
  line `(3) The number of members required to make a quorum at any meeting of the Committee shall be`
  line `one-third of its members.`
  line
  line `(4) All matters shall be decided by a majority of votes of the members present and, in the event of an`
  line `equality of votes, the Chairperson or other person presiding shall have a casting vote.`
  line
  line `(5) The Committee shall observe such rules of procedure in regard to the transaction of business at its`
  line `meetings as may be determined by bye-laws.`
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (10301)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 11
  title `Appointment of Standing Committees and sub-committees.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_10_10_00011_200235_1517807322907&sectionId=10301&sectionno=11&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_10_10_00011_200235_1517807322907
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Committee shall appoint`
  line `two Standing Committees, each headed by a Vice-Chairperson of the Committee, to deal with matters`
  line `relating to finance and Haj arrangements, from amongst its member consisting of such number of`
  line `members and with such powers and functions as may be determined by bye-laws made in this behalf by`
  line `the Committee:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Chairperson shall preside over the meeting of the Standing Committee in case he`
  line `attends the meeting.`
  line
  line `(2) The Committee may also appoint other sub-committees for such purposes as it may think fit and`
  line `any such sub-committee shall consist of such number of members and other persons as may be`
  line `determined by bye-laws made in this behalf by the Committee.`
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (10302)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 12
  title `Disqualification for being nominated, or for continuing, as a member of Committee.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_10_10_00011_200235_1517807322907&sectionId=10302&sectionno=12&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_10_10_00011_200235_1517807322907
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `A person shall be disqualified for being nominated, or for continuing as a member of the`
  line `Committee, if he--`
  line
  line `(i) is not a citizen of India;`
  line
  line `(ii) is not a Muslim, except for ex officio members as provided in clause (iii) of section 4;`
  line
  line `(iii) is less than twenty-five years of age;`
  line
  line `(iv) is of unsound mind and stands so declared by a competent court;`
  line
  line `(v) is an undischarged insolvent;`
  line
  line `(vi) has been convicted of an offence which, in the opinion of the Central Government, involves a`
  line `moral turpitude;`
  line
  line `(vii) has been on a previous occasion--`
  line
  line `(a) removed from his office as a member; or`
  line
  line `(b) removed by an order of a competent authority either for not acting in the interest of the`
  line `pilgrims or for corruption.`
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (10303)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 13
  title `Resignation of Chairperson, Vice-Chairperson and members.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_10_10_00011_200235_1517807322907&sectionId=10303&sectionno=13&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_10_10_00011_200235_1517807322907
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `The Chairperson, the`
  line `Vice-Chairperson or any other member may resign his office by writing under his hand addressed to the`
  line `Central Government and it shall be effective from the date of such resignation.`
obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (10304)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 14
  title `Removal of Chairperson, Vice-Chairperson and members.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_10_10_00011_200235_1517807322907&sectionId=10304&sectionno=14&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_10_10_00011_200235_1517807322907
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government`
  line `may, by notification in the Official Gazette, remove the Chairperson, a Vice-Chairperson of the`
  line `Committee or any member thereof, if he--`
  line
  line `(i) is or becomes subject to any of the disqualifications specified in section 12; or`
  line
  line `(ii) refuses to act or is incapable of acting or acts in a manner which the Central Government,`
  line `after hearing any explanation that he may offer, considers to be prejudicial to the interests of the`
  line `Committee or the interests of the pilgrims; or`
  line
  line `(iii) fails, in the opinion of the Committee, to attend three consecutive meetings of the`
  line `Committee, without sufficient excuse.`
  line
  line `(2) Where the Chairperson or a Vice-Chairperson of the Committee is removed under sub-section (1),`
  line `he shall also cease to be a member of the Committee.`
obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (10305)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 15
  title `Filling of a casual vacancy.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_10_10_00011_200235_1517807322907&sectionId=10305&sectionno=15&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_10_10_00011_200235_1517807322907
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `(1) When the seat of a member becomes vacant by his removal,`
  line `resignation, death or otherwise, a new member shall be nominated or elected, as the case may be, in his`
  line `place and such member shall hold office so long as the member whose place he fills would have been`
  line `entitled to hold office if such vacancy had not occurred.`
  line
  line `(2) Any casual vacancy under sub-section (1) shall be filled up by the same category to which the`
  line `former member belonged.`
obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (10306)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 16
  title `Chief Executive Officer and other employees.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_10_10_00011_200235_1517807322907&sectionId=10306&sectionno=16&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_10_10_00011_200235_1517807322907
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government shall appoint a`
  line `person, from a panel of Muslim officers of the Central Government and of the State Governments not`
  line `below the rank of Deputy Secretary to the Government of India, to be the Chief Executive Officer of the`
  line `Committee on such terms and conditions as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(2) The Chief Executive Officer shall be the ex officio Secretary of the Committee.`
  line
  line `(3) The Chief Executive Officer shall be appointed for a period of three years, which may be`
  line `extended by a maximum period of one year by the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(4) The Chief Executive Officer shall execute the decisions of the Committee and perform such other`
  line `functions as may be prescribed:`
  line
  line `Provided that in case of any difference of opinion between the Chief Executive Officer and the`
  line `Committee, he shall bring the matter to the notice of the Central Government, whose decision thereon`
  line `shall be final.`
  line
  line `(5) The Committee may, with the previous sanction of the Central Government, employ such other`
  line `officers and employees as it deems necessary to carry out the purposes of this Act, on such terms and`
  line `conditions as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_17:
  sectionId (10307)
  sectionNo (17)
  orderNo 17
  title `Establishment and incorporation of State Haj Committee.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_10_10_00011_200235_1517807322907&sectionId=10307&sectionno=17&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_10_10_00011_200235_1517807322907
obj_root_law_sections_17_content:
  string
  line `(1) With effect from such date as`
  line `the Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, appoint in this behalf, the`
  line `Government of a State shall constitute a Committee by the name of the......[name of the State] Haj`
  line `Committee:`
  line
  line `Provided that in case it appears to the Central Government for any reasons that it is not necessary for`
  line `a State or Union territory to establish a Haj Committee, it may authorise the State Haj Committee of a`
  line `contiguous State to deal with those pilgrims and suggest suitable representation of those States and Union`
  line territories.
  line
  line `(2) The State Committee shall be a body corporate, by the name aforesaid, having perpetual`
  line `succession and a common seal with power, subject to the provisions of this Act, to acquire, hold and`
  line `dispose of property, both movable and immovable, to create a charitable trust or endowment, and to`
  line `contract and shall by the said name sue and be sued.`
  line
  line `(3) Notwithstanding anything contained in this Act, an agreement may be entered into--`
  line
  line `(a) by two or more Governments of contiguous States, or`
  line
  line `(b) by the Central Government (in respect of one or more Union territories) and one or more`
  line `Governments of States contiguous to such Union territory or Union territories,`
  line
  line `to be in force for such period and to be subject to renewal for such further period, if any, as may be`
  line `specified in the agreement to provide for the constitution of a Joint State Committee,--`
  line
  line `(i) in a case referred to in clause (a), for all the participating States, and`
  line
  line `(ii) in a case referred to in clause (b), for the participating Union territory or Union territories`
  line `and the State or States.`
  line
  line `(4) An agreement under this section shall be published, in a case referred to in clause (a) of`
  line `sub-section (2), in the Official Gazette of the participating States and in a case referred to in clause (b) of`
  line `that sub-section, in the Official Gazette of the participating Union territory or Union territories and`
  line `participating State or States.`
  line
  line `(5) Any reference in this Act to the State Committee shall, unless the context otherwise requires, be`
  line `construed as including a Joint State Committee.`
obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_18:
  sectionId (10308)
  sectionNo (18)
  orderNo 18
  title `Composition of State Committee.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_10_10_00011_200235_1517807322907&sectionId=10308&sectionno=18&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_10_10_00011_200235_1517807322907
obj_root_law_sections_18_content:
  string
  line `(1) A State Committee shall consist of sixteen members, to`
  line `be nominated by the State Government, namely:--`
  line
  line `(i) three members from the Muslim members of--`
  line
  line `(a) Parliament representing the State;`
  line
  line `(b) State Legislative Assembly; and`
  line
  line `(c) Legislative Council, where it exists;`
  line
  line `(ii) three members from Muslim members representing local bodies in the State;`
  line
  line `(iii) three members having expertise in Muslim theology and law including one who shall be a`
  line `Shia Muslim;`
  line
  line `(iv) five members representing Muslim voluntary organisations working in the fields of public`
  line `administration, finance, education, culture or social work;`
  line
  line `(v) the Chairperson of the State Wakf Board; and`
  line
  line `(vi) Executive Officer of the State Committee, who shall be the ex officio member of the State`
  line `Committee:`
  line
  line `Provided that a Committee for any Union territory or a Joint State Committee shall consist of such`
  line `number of members as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(2) In case where there is no Muslim member in any of the categories mentioned in clauses (i) and (ii)`
  line `of sub-section (1), or where there is no Legislative Council in a State, nomination may be made in such`
  line `manner as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_19:
  sectionId (10309)
  sectionNo (19)
  orderNo 19
  title `Notification of members.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_10_10_00011_200235_1517807322907&sectionId=10309&sectionno=19&orderno=19&orgactid=AC_CEN_10_10_00011_200235_1517807322907
obj_root_law_sections_19_content:
  string
  line `As soon as may be after the nomination of the members of a State`
  line `Committee under sub-section (1) of section 18, the State Government shall publish, in the Official`
  line `Gazette of that State, the names of all such members.`
obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_20:
  sectionId (10310)
  sectionNo (20)
  orderNo 20
  title `Term of office.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_10_10_00011_200235_1517807322907&sectionId=10310&sectionno=20&orderno=20&orgactid=AC_CEN_10_10_00011_200235_1517807322907
obj_root_law_sections_20_content:
  string
  line `(1) The term of office of the members of the State Committee (other than the ex`
  line `officio members and members filling casual vacancies) shall be three years, commencing on the day`
  line `following the publication of the list of members under section 19.`
  line
  line `(2) The allowances payable to, and the other terms and conditions of the Chairperson and members`
  line `shall be such as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_21:
  sectionId (10311)
  sectionNo (21)
  orderNo 21
  title Chairperson.
  content obj_root_law_sections_21_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_10_10_00011_200235_1517807322907&sectionId=10311&sectionno=21&orderno=21&orgactid=AC_CEN_10_10_00011_200235_1517807322907
obj_root_law_sections_21_content:
  string
  line `(1) After the publication of the names of members of the State Committee under`
  line `section 19, the State Government shall convene within forty-five days the first meeting of the State`
  line `Committee at which the State Committee shall elect a Chairperson from amongst its members:`
  line
  line `Provided that an ex officio member shall not take part in the election of the Chairperson.`
  line
  line `(2) If the State Committee fails to elect a Chairperson, the State Government may appoint a member`
  line `of the State Committee to be the Chairperson thereof.`
  line
  line `(3) The election of the Chairperson shall be notified by the State Government in the Official Gazette`
  line `of the State.`
  line
  line `(4) The term of office of the Chairperson shall be three years and no person shall hold the office of`
  line `the Chairperson for more than two consecutive terms.`
  line
  line `(5) Any casual vacancy in the office of the Chairperson shall be filled in accordance with`
  line `sub-section (1) or sub-section (2), as the case may be.`
obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_22:
  sectionId (10312)
  sectionNo (22)
  orderNo 22
  title `Reconstitution of a State Committee.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_10_10_00011_200235_1517807322907&sectionId=10312&sectionno=22&orderno=22&orgactid=AC_CEN_10_10_00011_200235_1517807322907
obj_root_law_sections_22_content:
  string
  line `(1) The State Government shall take or cause to be`
  line `taken all necessary steps for the reconstitution of a new State Committee at least four months before the`
  line `expiry of the term of the State Committee.`
  line
  line `(2) An outgoing member shall be eligible for re-nomination of the State Committee for not more than`
  line `two terms:`
  line
  line `Provided that fifty per cent. of the nominees may be re-nominated for a second term in such manner`
  line `as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_23:
  sectionId (10313)
  sectionNo (23)
  orderNo 23
  title `Disqualification for being nominated, or for continuing, as a member of the Committee.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_10_10_00011_200235_1517807322907&sectionId=10313&sectionno=23&orderno=23&orgactid=AC_CEN_10_10_00011_200235_1517807322907
obj_root_law_sections_23_content:
  string
  line A
  line `person shall be disqualified for being nominated, or for continuing, as a member of the State Committee,`
  line `if he--`
  line
  line `(i) is not a citizen of India;`
  line
  line `(ii) is not a resident of that State;`
  line
  line `(iii) is not a Muslim, except for an Executive Officer as provided in clause (vi) of sub-section (1)`
  line `of section 18;`
  line
  line `(iv) is less than twenty-five years of age;`
  line
  line `(v) is of unsound mind and stands so declared by a competent court;`
  line
  line `(vi) is an undischarged insolvent;`
  line
  line `(vii) has been convicted of an offence which, in the opinion of the State Government, involves a`
  line `moral turpitude;`
  line
  line `(viii) has been on a previous occasion--`
  line
  line `(a) removed from his office as a member; or`
  line
  line `(b) removed by an order of a competent authority either for not acting in the interest of the`
  line `pilgrims or for corruption.`
obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_24:
  sectionId (10314)
  sectionNo (24)
  orderNo 24
  title `Resignation of Chairperson and members.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_24_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_10_10_00011_200235_1517807322907&sectionId=10314&sectionno=24&orderno=24&orgactid=AC_CEN_10_10_00011_200235_1517807322907
obj_root_law_sections_24_content:
  string
  line `The Chairperson or any other member may resign`
  line `his office by writing under his hand addressed to the State Government and it shall be effective from the`
  line `date of such resignation.`
obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_25:
  sectionId (10315)
  sectionNo (25)
  orderNo 25
  title `Removal of Chairperson and members.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_25_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_10_10_00011_200235_1517807322907&sectionId=10315&sectionno=25&orderno=25&orgactid=AC_CEN_10_10_00011_200235_1517807322907
obj_root_law_sections_25_content:
  string
  line `(1) The State Government may, by notification in the`
  line `Official Gazette, remove the Chairperson of the State Committee or any member thereof, if he--`
  line
  line `(i) is or becomes subject to any of the disqualifications specified in section 23; or`
  line
  line `(ii) refuses to act or is incapable of acting or acts in a manner which the State Government, after`
  line `hearing any explanation that he may offer, considers to be prejudicial to the interests of the State`
  line `Committee or the interests of the pilgrims; or`
  line
  line `(iii) fails, in the opinion of the State Committee, to attend three consecutive meetings of the State`
  line `Committee, without sufficient excuse.`
  line
  line `(2) Where the Chairperson of the State Committee is removed under sub-section (1), he shall also`
  line `cease to be a member of the State Committee.`
obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_26:
  sectionId (10316)
  sectionNo (26)
  orderNo 26
  title `Filling of a casual vacancy.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_26_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_10_10_00011_200235_1517807322907&sectionId=10316&sectionno=26&orderno=26&orgactid=AC_CEN_10_10_00011_200235_1517807322907
obj_root_law_sections_26_content:
  string
  line `(1) When the seat of a member becomes vacant by his removal,`
  line `resignation, death or otherwise, a new member shall be nominated in his place and such member shall`
  line `hold office so long as the member whose place he fills would have been entitled to hold office if such`
  line `vacancy had not occurred.`
  line
  line `(2) Any casual vacancy under sub-section (1) shall be filled up by the same category to which the`
  line `former member belonged.`
obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_27:
  sectionId (10317)
  sectionNo (27)
  orderNo 27
  title `Duties of State Committee.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_27_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_10_10_00011_200235_1517807322907&sectionId=10317&sectionno=27&orderno=27&orgactid=AC_CEN_10_10_00011_200235_1517807322907
obj_root_law_sections_27_content:
  string
  line `(1) It shall be the duty of a State Committee to implement the`
  line `policy and directions of the Committee in the interests of Haj pilgrims.`
  line
  line `(2) The State Committee shall provide assistance to the Haj pilgrims including in the matter of their`
  line `transport between their home States and the point of exit from India and their transit accommodation at`
  line `points of exit.`
  line
  line `(3) The State Committee shall discharge such other duties in connection with Haj as may be`
  line `prescribed by the State Government concerned, in consultation with the Central Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_28:
  sectionId (10318)
  sectionNo (28)
  orderNo 28
  title `Meetings of State Committee.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_28_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_10_10_00011_200235_1517807322907&sectionId=10318&sectionno=28&orderno=28&orgactid=AC_CEN_10_10_00011_200235_1517807322907
obj_root_law_sections_28_content:
  string
  line `(1) A State Committee shall meet at least twice in a year before`
  line `the Haj day and once after the Haj is over.`
  line
  line `(2) The number of members required to make a quorum at any meeting of the State Committee shall`
  line `be one-third of its members.`
  line
  line `(3) In addition to the number of meetings specified in sub-section (1), the State Committee may hold`
  line `meetings as and when requisitioned by at least one-third of its members or when considered necessary by`
  line `the Chairperson.`
  line
  line `(4) All matters shall be decided by a majority of votes of the members present and, in the event of an`
  line `equality of votes, the Chairperson or other person presiding shall have a casting vote.`
obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_29:
  sectionId (10319)
  sectionNo (29)
  orderNo 29
  title `Executive Officer and other employees of State Committee.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_29_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_10_10_00011_200235_1517807322907&sectionId=10319&sectionno=29&orderno=29&orgactid=AC_CEN_10_10_00011_200235_1517807322907
obj_root_law_sections_29_content:
  string
  line `(1) The State Government shall`
  line `appoint a person, from amongst its officers not below the rank of Deputy Secretary, to be the Executive`
  line `Officer of the State Committee:`
  line
  line `Provided that the person so appointed shall preferably be a Muslim.`
  line
  line `(2) The Executive Officer of the State Committee shall act as its Secretary.`
  line
  line `(3) The Executive Officer shall execute the decisions of the State Committee and perform such other`
  line `functions as may be prescribed:`
  line
  line `Provided that in case of any difference of opinion between the Executive Officer and the State`
  line `Committee, he shall bring the matter to the notice of the State Government whose decision thereon shall`
  line `be final.`
  line
  line `(4) The State Committee shall, with the previous sanction of the State Government, employ such`
  line `officers and other employees as it deems necessary to carry out the purposes of this Act.`
  line
  line `(5) The term of office and conditions of service of officers and other employees shall be such as may`
  line `be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_30:
  sectionId (10320)
  sectionNo (30)
  orderNo 30
  title `Central Haj Fund.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_30_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_10_10_00011_200235_1517807322907&sectionId=10320&sectionno=30&orderno=30&orgactid=AC_CEN_10_10_00011_200235_1517807322907
obj_root_law_sections_30_content:
  string
  line `The Committee shall have its own Fund to be called the Central Haj Fund,`
  line `and there shall be placed to the credit thereof the following sums, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) sums realised from any fees and service charges which may be levied by the Committee:--`
  line
  line `(i) for registration of applications for Haj; and`
  line
  line `(ii) for issue of Haj pilgrim travel passes;`
  line
  line `(b) money collected from pilgrims for performance of Haj;`
  line
  line `(c) the income from all deposits and investment of the Committee's funds;`
  line
  line `(d) the sums realised from the sale of the effects of deceased pilgrims and sums of money left by`
  line `them, which are unclaimed and have lapsed to the Central Government;`
  line
  line `(e) any sums loaned by the Central or a State Government, or any other source approved by the`
  line Government;
  line
  line `(f) any amount that may be legally due to the Committee from any source; and`
  line
  line `(g) the amount standing at the commencement of this Act to the credit of the Haj Fund or the`
  line `Indigent Pilgrims Fund established under the Haj Committee Act, 1959 (51 of 1959).`
obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_31:
  sectionId (10321)
  sectionNo (31)
  orderNo 31
  title `Application of Central Haj Fund.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_31_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_10_10_00011_200235_1517807322907&sectionId=10321&sectionno=31&orderno=31&orgactid=AC_CEN_10_10_00011_200235_1517807322907
obj_root_law_sections_31_content:
  string
  line `The Central Haj Fund shall, subject to the provisions of this`
  line `Act and the rules made thereunder, be under the control and management of the Committee, and shall be`
  line `applied to the following purposes, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) pay and allowances of the Chief Executive Officer and other employees of the Committee;`
  line
  line `(b) payment of charges and expenses incidental to the objects specified in section 9; and`
  line
  line `(c) any other expenses which are required to be met by the Committee or a State Committee, as`
  line `approved by the Central Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_32:
  sectionId (10322)
  sectionNo (32)
  orderNo 32
  title `State Haj Fund.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_32_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_10_10_00011_200235_1517807322907&sectionId=10322&sectionno=32&orderno=32&orgactid=AC_CEN_10_10_00011_200235_1517807322907
obj_root_law_sections_32_content:
  string
  line `The State Committee shall have its own fund to be called the State Haj Fund`
  line `and the following sums shall be placed to the credit thereof, namely:--`
  line
  line `(i) all sums of money paid to it or any grant made by the Committee for the purposes of this Act;`
  line
  line `(ii) any grant or loan that may be made to the State Committee by the State Government, or any`
  line `other source for the purposes of this Act, as approved by the State Government;`
  line
  line `(iii) any amount that may be legally due to the State Committee from any source; and`
  line
  line `(iv) the moneys, if any, standing to the credit of a State Haj Committee, at the commencement of`
  line `this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_33:
  sectionId (10323)
  sectionNo (33)
  orderNo 33
  title `Application of State Haj Fund.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_33_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_10_10_00011_200235_1517807322907&sectionId=10323&sectionno=33&orderno=33&orgactid=AC_CEN_10_10_00011_200235_1517807322907
obj_root_law_sections_33_content:
  string
  line `The State Haj Fund shall, subject to any rules that may be`
  line `made under this Act, be under the control and management of the State Committee and shall be applied to`
  line `the following purposes, namely:--`
  line
  line `(i) pay and allowances of the employees of the State Committee other than its Executive Officer`
  line `whose pay and allowances shall be borne by the State Government;`
  line
  line `(ii) payment of charges and expenses incidental to the due performance of its duties by the State`
  line `Committee for the objects specified in section 27; and`
  line
  line `(iii) any other expenses, as approved by the State Government which are required to be met by`
  line `the State Committee.`
obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_34:
  sectionId (10324)
  sectionNo (34)
  orderNo 34
  title `Accounts and audit.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_34_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_10_10_00011_200235_1517807322907&sectionId=10324&sectionno=34&orderno=34&orgactid=AC_CEN_10_10_00011_200235_1517807322907
obj_root_law_sections_34_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Committee and every State Committee shall maintain proper`
  line `accounts and other relevant records and prepare an annual statement of accounts, in such form as may be`
  line `prescribed by the Central Government, or as the case may be, the State Government.`
  line
  line `(2) The accounts shall be examined and audited annually by such auditors as the Central Government`
  line `or, as the case may be, the State Government may approve.`
  line
  line `(3) The accounts of the Committee or the State Committee as certified by the auditor together with`
  line `the audit report thereon shall be forwarded annually by the said Committee to the Central Government, or`
  line `as the case may be, the State Government.`
  line
  line `(4) The Central Government shall, as soon as may be after the receipt of the audit report under`
  line `sub-section (3), cause the same to be laid before each House of Parliament.`
  line
  line `(5) The State Government shall, as soon as may be, after the receipt of the audit report under`
  line `sub-section (3), cause the same to be laid before the State Legislature.`
obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_35:
  sectionId (10325)
  sectionNo (35)
  orderNo 35
  title `Powers of Committee to issue Pilgrim Passes and levy fees.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_35_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_10_10_00011_200235_1517807322907&sectionId=10325&sectionno=35&orderno=35&orgactid=AC_CEN_10_10_00011_200235_1517807322907
obj_root_law_sections_35_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Committee shall have the`
  line `power to issue a travel document called "Pilgrim Pass" to a Haj pilgrim for his departure from India as a`
  line `bona fide pilgrim to Saudi Arabia and the said Pilgrim shall be deemed to be exempted from the`
  line `provisions of section 3 of the Passports Act, 1967 (15 of 1967).`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in the Passports Act, 1967 (15 of 1967), the Central`
  line `Government may, in consultation with the Committee, levy such fees for registration of Haj pilgrims,`
  line `issuance of Pilgrim Pass by the Committee and other related matters, as may be prescribed in connection`
  line `with rendering of such services.`
obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_36:
  sectionId (10326)
  sectionNo (36)
  orderNo 36
  title `Supersession of Committee.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_36_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_10_10_00011_200235_1517807322907&sectionId=10326&sectionno=36&orderno=36&orgactid=AC_CEN_10_10_00011_200235_1517807322907
obj_root_law_sections_36_content:
  string
  line `(1) If, in the opinion of the Central Government, the Committee is`
  line `unable to perform, or persistently makes default in the performance of the duties imposed on it by or`
  line `under this Act or exceeds or abuses its powers, the Central Government may, by an order published,`
  line `together with a statement of the reasons therefor, in the Official Gazette, supersede it for such period as`
  line `may be specified in the order:`
  line
  line `Provided that before making an order of supersession as aforesaid, the Central Government shall give`
  line `a reasonable opportunity to the Committee to show cause why it should not be superseded.`
  line
  line `(2) When the Committee is superseded by an order under sub-section (1),--`
  line
  line `(a) all members shall, on such date as may be specified in the order, vacate their offices as such`
  line `members without prejudice to their eligibility for nomination under clause (d);`
  line
  line `(b) during the period of supersession of the Committee, all powers and duties conferred and`
  line `imposed upon the Committee by or under this Act shall be exercised and performed by such officer or`
  line `authority as the Central Government may appoint in that behalf;`
  line
  line `(c) all property vested in the Committee shall, until it is reconstituted, vest in the Central`
  line Government;
  line
  line `(d) before the expiry of the period of supersession, nominations shall be made by the Central`
  line `Government for the purpose of reconstituting the Committee.`
  line
  line `(3) An order of supersession made under this section together with a statement of the reasons therefor`
  line `shall be laid before each House of Parliament as soon as may be after it has been made.`
  line
  line `(4) A State Government may exercise the same powers and duties in respect of a State Committee as`
  line `mentioned in sub-sections (1), (2) and (3) of this section subject to the conditions mentioned therein and`
  line `any directions issued by the Central Government in this regard.`
obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_37:
  sectionId (10327)
  sectionNo (37)
  orderNo 37
  title `Membership of Committee or State Committee not to constitute office of profit.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_37_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_10_10_00011_200235_1517807322907&sectionId=10327&sectionno=37&orderno=37&orgactid=AC_CEN_10_10_00011_200235_1517807322907
obj_root_law_sections_37_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding anything contained in any other law for the time being in force, the office of a`
  line `member of the Committee or State Committee shall not be deemed to be an office of profit.`
obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_38:
  sectionId (10328)
  sectionNo (38)
  orderNo 38
  title `Vacancies, etc., not to invalidate proceedings of Committee.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_38_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_38_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_10_10_00011_200235_1517807322907&sectionId=10328&sectionno=38&orderno=38&orgactid=AC_CEN_10_10_00011_200235_1517807322907
obj_root_law_sections_38_content:
  string
  line `No act or proceeding of the`
  line `Committee or of a State Committee or of a Joint State Committee, as the case may be, shall be invalid by`
  line `reason only of the existence of any vacancy amongst its members, or any defect in the constitution`
  line thereof.
obj_root_law_sections_38_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_39:
  sectionId (10329)
  sectionNo (39)
  orderNo 39
  title `Officers and employees of Committee to be public servants.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_39_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_39_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_10_10_00011_200235_1517807322907&sectionId=10329&sectionno=39&orderno=39&orgactid=AC_CEN_10_10_00011_200235_1517807322907
obj_root_law_sections_39_content:
  string
  line `The officers and employees of`
  line `the Committees and other persons duly appointed to discharge any duty under this Act or rules or`
  line `bye-laws made thereunder, shall be deemed to be public servants within the meaning of section 21 of the`
  line `Indian Penal Code (45 of 1860).`
obj_root_law_sections_39_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_40:
  sectionId (10330)
  sectionNo (40)
  orderNo 40
  title Indemnity.
  content obj_root_law_sections_40_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_40_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_10_10_00011_200235_1517807322907&sectionId=10330&sectionno=40&orderno=40&orgactid=AC_CEN_10_10_00011_200235_1517807322907
obj_root_law_sections_40_content:
  string
  line `No suit, prosecution or other legal proceeding shall lie against the Chairperson,`
  line `Vice-Chairpersons or any member of the Committee or a State Committee in respect of anything in good`
  line `faith done or purporting to have been done under this Act, except with the prior permission of the Central`
  line `or State Government, as the case may be.`
obj_root_law_sections_40_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_41:
  sectionId (10331)
  sectionNo (41)
  orderNo 41
  title `Power to amend Schedule.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_41_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_41_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_10_10_00011_200235_1517807322907&sectionId=10331&sectionno=41&orderno=41&orgactid=AC_CEN_10_10_00011_200235_1517807322907
obj_root_law_sections_41_content:
  string
  line `(1) If the Central Government is satisfied that it is necessary or`
  line `expedient so to do, it may, by notification published in the Official Gazette, amend the Schedule and`
  line `thereupon the Schedule shall be deemed to have been amended accordingly.`
  line
  line `(2) A copy of every notification made under sub-section (1) shall be laid before each House of`
  line `Parliament as soon as may be after it is made.`
obj_root_law_sections_41_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_42:
  sectionId (10332)
  sectionNo (42)
  orderNo 42
  title `Redressal of grievances.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_42_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_42_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_10_10_00011_200235_1517807322907&sectionId=10332&sectionno=42&orderno=42&orgactid=AC_CEN_10_10_00011_200235_1517807322907
obj_root_law_sections_42_content:
  string
  line `Any Haj pilgrim, who is aggrieved by the discharge of any of the`
  line `duties performed by the Haj Committee or the State Haj Committee, shall make a representation for the`
  line `redressal of his grievance to the Haj Committee or the State Haj Committee, as the case may be, and the`
  line `same shall be disposed of by the said Committee, if necessary, after hearing the aggrieved person.`
obj_root_law_sections_42_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_43:
  sectionId (10333)
  sectionNo (43)
  orderNo 43
  title `Vesting of properties and other rights, etc., in Committees.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_43_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_43_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_10_10_00011_200235_1517807322907&sectionId=10333&sectionno=43&orderno=43&orgactid=AC_CEN_10_10_00011_200235_1517807322907
obj_root_law_sections_43_content:
  string
  line `(1) On and from the`
  line `commencement of this Act, all assets, rights, leaseholds, powers, authorities and privileges and all`
  line `properties, movable and immovable, including lands, buildings, stores, cash balances, cash on hand,`
  line `reserve funds, investments and all other rights and interests in or arising out of such properties as were`
  line `immediately before such commencement in the ownership, power or control of Haj Committee, Mumbai,`
  line `constituted under the Haj Committee Act, 1959 (51 of 1959) and all books of account, registers and all`
  line `other documents of whatever nature relating thereto shall vest absolutely in and belong to the Committee.`
  line
  line `(2) On and from the commencement of this Act, all assets, rights, leaseholds, powers, authorities and`
  line `privileges and all properties, movable and immovable, including lands, buildings, stores, cash balances,`
  line `cash on hand, reserve funds, investments and all other rights and interests in or arising out of such`
  line `properties as were immediately before such commencement in the ownership, power or control of Haj`
  line `Committee of a State and, all books of account, registers and all other documents of whatever nature`
  line `relating thereto shall vest absolutely in and belong to the Haj Committee of a State.`
  line
  line `(3) All debts, obligations and liabilities incurred, all contracts entered into and all matters and things`
  line `engaged to be done by, with or for the Committee or a State Committee immediately before such`
  line `commencement for or in connection with the purposes of the Committee or a State Committee shall be`
  line `deemed to have been incurred, entered into and engaged to be done by, with or for the Committee or a`
  line `State Committee, as the case may be.`
  line
  line `(4) All sums of money due to the Committee or a State Committee immediately before such`
  line `commencement shall be deemed to be due to the Committee or a State Committee, as the case may be.`
  line
  line `(5) All contracts made with and all instruments executed on behalf of the Haj Committee, Mumbai or`
  line `the Haj Committee of a State shall be deemed to have been made or executed on behalf of the Committee,`
  line `or as the case may be, the State Committee and shall be performed accordingly.`
  line
  line `(6) In all suits and legal proceedings pending on the commencement of this Act in or to which the Haj`
  line `Committee, Mumbai or the Haj Committee of a State was a party, the Committee, or as the case may be,`
  line `the State Committee shall be deemed to have been substituted therefor.`
obj_root_law_sections_43_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_44:
  sectionId (10334)
  sectionNo (44)
  orderNo 44
  title `Power to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_44_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_44_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_10_10_00011_200235_1517807322907&sectionId=10334&sectionno=44&orderno=44&orgactid=AC_CEN_10_10_00011_200235_1517807322907
obj_root_law_sections_44_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, by notification, make rules to carry`
  line `out the purposes of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular, and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing powers, such rules may`
  line `provide for all or any of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(i) the manner of election of members of the Committee under clause (ii) of section 4;`
  line
  line `(ii) the terms and conditions of the Chairperson and members under sub-section (2) of section 6;`
  line
  line `(iii) the powers and duties of the Chairperson under sub-section (3) of section 7;`
  line
  line `(iv) the manner in which the members may be re-nominated under the proviso to sub-section (2)`
  line `of section 8;`
  line
  line `(v) duties in connection with Haj under clause (ix) of sub-section (1) of section 9;`
  line
  line `(vi) the functions of the Chief Executive Officer and the terms and conditions of service of the`
  line `Chief Executive Officer and other employees of the Committee under section 16;`
  line
  line `(vii) the number of members of a Joint State Committee or of a Committee for Union territory`
  line `under the proviso to clause (vi) of sub-section (1) of section 18;`
  line
  line `(viii) the manner in which the accounts shall be maintained by the Committee and the State`
  line `Committees and the audit of such accounts under section 34;`
  line
  line `(ix) issue of Haj Pilgrim Pass under sub-section (1) of section 35;`
  line
  line `(x) amendment of the Schedule relating to the zones comprising contiguous States or Union`
  line `territories under section 41;`
  line
  line `(xi) any other matter which may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(3) Every rule made under this section shall be laid, as soon as may be after it is made, before each`
  line `House of Parliament, while it is in session for a total period of thirty days which may be comprised in one`
  line `session or in two or more successive sessions , and if, before the expiry of the session in which it is so`
  line `laid, or the session immediately following, both Houses agree in making any modification in the rule or`
  line `both Houses agree that the rule should not be made, the rule shall thereafter have effect only in such`
  line `modified form or be of no effect, as the case may be; so, however, that any such modification or`
  line `annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of anything previously done under that rule.`
obj_root_law_sections_44_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_45:
  sectionId (10335)
  sectionNo (45)
  orderNo 45
  title `Power to make bye-laws.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_45_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_45_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_10_10_00011_200235_1517807322907&sectionId=10335&sectionno=45&orderno=45&orgactid=AC_CEN_10_10_00011_200235_1517807322907
obj_root_law_sections_45_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Committee may, by notification, make bye-laws consistent`
  line `with the provisions of the Act and the rules made thereunder in respect of the following matters,`
  line `namely:--`
  line
  line `(i) powers and duties of the Vice-Chairpersons under sub-section (4) of section 7;`
  line
  line `(ii) providing for the publication of the proceedings of the Committee and any matter of interests`
  line `to pilgrims under clause (viii) of sub-section (1) of section 9;`
  line
  line `(iii) laying down the rules of procedure for transaction of business at meeting of the Committee`
  line `under sub-section (5) of section 10;`
  line
  line `(iv) powers and functions of the Standing Committee and determination of number of members`
  line `and other persons in sub-committees under section 11;`
  line
  line `(v) providing for any other matter which the Committee deems necessary for giving effect to the`
  line `provisions of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) Bye-laws made by the Committee under this section shall be submitted to the Central Government`
  line `and shall not take effect until they have been confirmed by the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(3) Bye-laws which have been confirmed by the Central Government shall be published in the`
  line `Official Gazette.`
obj_root_law_sections_45_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_46:
  sectionId (10336)
  sectionNo (46)
  orderNo 46
  title `Power to delegate.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_46_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_46_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_10_10_00011_200235_1517807322907&sectionId=10336&sectionno=46&orderno=46&orgactid=AC_CEN_10_10_00011_200235_1517807322907
obj_root_law_sections_46_content:
  string
  line `Subject to the provisions of this Act and the rules made thereunder, the`
  line `Committee may, by general or special order in writing, with the prior approval of the Central`
  line `Government, delegate to any member or Chief Executive Officer on the Committee, and subject to such`
  line `conditions and limitations, as may be specified in the order, such of its powers under this Act (except the`
  line `powers to make bye-laws under section 45) as it may deem necessary.`
obj_root_law_sections_46_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_47:
  sectionId (10337)
  sectionNo (47)
  orderNo 47
  title `Power to make rules by State Governments.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_47_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_47_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_10_10_00011_200235_1517807322907&sectionId=10337&sectionno=47&orderno=47&orgactid=AC_CEN_10_10_00011_200235_1517807322907
obj_root_law_sections_47_content:
  string
  line `(1) The State Governments may, in consultation`
  line `with the Central Government, by notification make rules to carry out the purposes of this Act in respect of`
  line `the State Committees.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular, and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing powers, such rules may`
  line `provide for all or any of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(i) terms and conditions of the Chairperson and members of the State Committee under sub-section (2) of section 20;`
  line
  line `(ii) the manner in which the members may be re-nominated under the proviso to sub-section (2) of section 22;`
  line
  line `(iii) duties of the State Committee under sub-section (3) of section 27;`
  line
  line `(iv) the functions of the Executive Officer and the terms and conditions of service of officers and`
  line `other employees under section 29;`
  line
  line `(v) any other matter which is required to be or may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(3) Every rule made under this section shall be laid, as soon as may be after it is made, before the`
  line `State Legislature.`
obj_root_law_sections_47_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_48:
  sectionId (10338)
  sectionNo (48)
  orderNo 48
  title `Provisions as to employees of the existing Committee before the commencement of this Act.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_48_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_48_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_10_10_00011_200235_1517807322907&sectionId=10338&sectionno=48&orderno=48&orgactid=AC_CEN_10_10_00011_200235_1517807322907
obj_root_law_sections_48_content:
  string
  line `Every officer and other employee of any of the existing Committee and the State Committee, as the`
  line `case may be, shall, on and from the commencement of this Act, stand transferred to or become an officer`
  line `or other employee of the Committee or the State Committee, as the case may be, with such designation as`
  line `such Committee may determine and shall hold office or service therein by the same tenure, at the same`
  line `remuneration, upon the same terms and conditions of service as he would have held under the Haj`
  line `Committee constituted under the Haj Committee Act, 1959 (51 of 1959) and shall continue to do so as an`
  line `officer or other employee of the Committee till such time the terms and conditions are duly altered by`
  line `such Committee:`
  line
  line `Provided that the tenure, remuneration and terms and conditions of service of any such officer or`
  line `other employee of the Committee or of a State Committee, as the case may be, shall not be altered to his disadvantage without the previous sanction of the Central Government or State Government, as the case`
  line `may be:`
  line
  line `Provided further that any service rendered by any such officer or other employee before the`
  line `commencement of this Act shall be deemed to be the service rendered under the Committee or, as the`
  line `case may be, the State Committee.`
obj_root_law_sections_48_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_49:
  sectionId (10339)
  sectionNo (49)
  orderNo 49
  title `Protection of action taken in good faith.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_49_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_49_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_10_10_00011_200235_1517807322907&sectionId=10339&sectionno=49&orderno=49&orgactid=AC_CEN_10_10_00011_200235_1517807322907
obj_root_law_sections_49_content:
  string
  line `No suit, prosecution or other legal proceedings shall`
  line `lie against the Government or any officer or other employee of the Government or the Committee`
  line `constituted under this Act in respect of anything which is in good faith done or intended to be done under`
  line `this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_49_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_50:
  sectionId (10340)
  sectionNo (50)
  orderNo 50
  title `Power to remove difficulties.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_50_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_50_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_10_10_00011_200235_1517807322907&sectionId=10340&sectionno=50&orderno=50&orgactid=AC_CEN_10_10_00011_200235_1517807322907
obj_root_law_sections_50_content:
  string
  line `(1) If any difficulty arises in giving effect to the provisions of`
  line `this Act, the Central Government may, by order not inconsistent with the provisions of this Act, remove`
  line `the difficulty:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such order shall be made after the expiry of a period of two years from the`
  line `commencement of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) Any order made under this section shall be laid, as soon as may be after it is made, before each`
  line `House of Parliament.`
obj_root_law_sections_50_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_51:
  sectionId (10341)
  sectionNo (51)
  orderNo 51
  title `Power to give directions.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_51_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_51_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_10_10_00011_200235_1517807322907&sectionId=10341&sectionno=51&orderno=51&orgactid=AC_CEN_10_10_00011_200235_1517807322907
obj_root_law_sections_51_content:
  string
  line `The Central Government may, in exercise of its powers and`
  line `performance of its functions under this Act, issue directions in writing to the Committee or the State`
  line `Government or the State Committee and such Committee, State Government or State Committee, as the`
  line `case may be, shall be bound to comply with such directions.`
obj_root_law_sections_51_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_52:
  sectionId (10342)
  sectionNo (52)
  orderNo 52
  title Repeal.
  content obj_root_law_sections_52_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_52_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_10_10_00011_200235_1517807322907&sectionId=10342&sectionno=52&orderno=52&orgactid=AC_CEN_10_10_00011_200235_1517807322907
obj_root_law_sections_52_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Haj Committee Act, 1959 (51 of 1959) is hereby repealed.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding such repeal, the Haj Committee constituted under the said Act shall, until the`
  line `establishment of the Committee under this Act, continue to function as if this Act had not been passed and`
  line `on such notification under section 5 on the establishment of the Committee, the former Committee shall`
  line `stand dissolved.`
  line
  line `(3) Notwithstanding such repeal, anything done or any action taken under the Haj Committee Act,`
  line `1959 (51 of 1959) shall be deemed to have been done or taken under the corresponding provisions of this`
  line Act.
obj_root_law_sections_52_footnotes:
  string
  line
